d3iIDTable.name: d3iIDTable
d3iIDTable.description: This table contains an entry for each of the manageable DS3 Ingress Cards in the chassis. It contains objects that reflect the current configuration of parameters that affect the operation of all the entities that reside on the given card.

d3iIDEntry.name: d3iIDEntry
d3iIDEntry.description: There is one Identification table entry per DS3 Card in the chassis.

d3iIDIndex.name: d3iIDIndex
d3iIDIndex.description: A unique value for each card in the chassis. The value of d3iIdIndex matches the value of the index for the corresponding card entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

d3iIDNACHardwareSerNum.name: d3iIDNACHardwareSerNum
d3iIDNACHardwareSerNum.description: This object contains DS3 NAC module hardware serial number as stored in EEPROM.

d3iIDNICHardwareSerNum.name: d3iIDNICHardwareSerNum
d3iIDNICHardwareSerNum.description: This object contains DS3 NIC module hardware serial number as stored in EEPROM.

d3iIDNACHardwareRev.name: d3iIDNACHardwareRev
d3iIDNACHardwareRev.description: This object contains DS3 NAC module hardware revision as stored in EEPROM.

d3iIDNICHardwareRev.name: d3iIDNICHardwareRev
d3iIDNICHardwareRev.description: This object contains DS3 NIC module hardware revision as stored in EEPROM.

d3iIDBoardManagerSwRev.name: d3iIDBoardManagerSwRev
d3iIDBoardManagerSwRev.description: This object contains revision of the software being executed by the DS3 NAC board manager processor.

d3iIDBoardManagerDate.name: d3iIDBoardManagerDate
d3iIDBoardManagerDate.description: This object contains board manager build date.

d3iCfgTable.name: d3iCfgTable
d3iCfgTable.description: This table contains an entry for each of the manageable DS3 Ingress Cards in the chassis. It contains objects that reflect the current configuration of parameters that affect the operation of all the entities that reside on the given card.

d3iCfgEntry.name: d3iCfgEntry
d3iCfgEntry.description: There is one Configuration table entry per DS3 Card in the chassis.

d3iCfgIndex.name: d3iCfgIndex
d3iCfgIndex.description: A unique value for each card in the chassis. The value of d3iCfgIndex matches the value of the index for the corresponding card entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

d3iCfgPrimaryTimeSource.name: d3iCfgPrimaryTimeSource
d3iCfgPrimaryTimeSource.description: This object contains Designation of primary system clock timing reference source.

d3iCfgSecondaryTimeSource.name: d3iCfgSecondaryTimeSource
d3iCfgSecondaryTimeSource.description: This object contains Designation of secondary system clock timing reference source.

d3iCfgTimeSourceSwitchMode.name: d3iCfgTimeSourceSwitchMode
d3iCfgTimeSourceSwitchMode.description: If a clock failure occurs on the currently active clock timing reference, this object specifies whether the switchover to the backup reference will be performed automatically or manually.

d3iCfgCLIPromptName.name: d3iCfgCLIPromptName
d3iCfgCLIPromptName.description: This object is used to identify DS3 module's console prompt name.

d3iStatTable.name: d3iStatTable
d3iStatTable.description: The Status table contains an entry for each DS3 card in the chassis.

d3iStatEntry.name: d3iStatEntry
d3iStatEntry.description: There is one entry for each DS3 card in the chassis.

d3iStatIndex.name: d3iStatIndex
d3iStatIndex.description: A unique value for each DS3 card in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding DS3 card's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

d3iStatSigPBusTxPktOkCnt.name: d3iStatSigPBusTxPktOkCnt
d3iStatSigPBusTxPktOkCnt.description: The number of successful packets transmitted over the signaling packet bus connection.

d3iStatSigPBusTxPktFldCnt.name: d3iStatSigPBusTxPktFldCnt
d3iStatSigPBusTxPktFldCnt.description: The number of packets failed to transmit over the signaling packet bus connection.

d3iStatSigPBusRxPktOkCnt.name: d3iStatSigPBusRxPktOkCnt
d3iStatSigPBusRxPktOkCnt.description: The number of successful packets received over the signaling packet bus connection.

d3iStatSigPBusRxPktRjtCnt.name: d3iStatSigPBusRxPktRjtCnt
d3iStatSigPBusRxPktRjtCnt.description: The number of packets rejected by the DS3 NAC module message handling application.

d3iStatSigPBusConnState.name: d3iStatSigPBusConnState
d3iStatSigPBusConnState.description: The state of the signaling packet bus connection to the JHDM NAC. The loopback state means the DS3 has been requested, over the signaling packet bus link, to loopback all of its signaling channel received data. It will stay in this state until the DS3 sends an call control message to remove the loopback on this signaling connection.

d3iStatEnfasLinkDownCause.name: d3iStatEnfasLinkDownCause
d3iStatEnfasLinkDownCause.description: The reason for the E-NFAS signaling link going down. DisCmd: A DISC command was received over the packet bus signaling link. NACRemoval: A chassis awareness message indicated that the NAC connected to the E-NFAS link has been removed.

d3iStatPbClock.name: d3iStatPbClock
d3iStatPbClock.description: This object defines the current status of the packet bus clock.

d3iStatTdmClock.name: d3iStatTdmClock
d3iStatTdmClock.description: This object defines the current status of the TDM bus system clock.

d3iCmdTable.name: d3iCmdTable
d3iCmdTable.description: The DS3 card command table contains an entry for each of the manageable DS3 card in the chassis. It provides a means through which to take specific actions on the DS3 card in the chassis.

d3iCmdEntry.name: d3iCmdEntry
d3iCmdEntry.description: There is one DS3 card command entry per DS3 card in the chassis.

d3iCmdIndex.name: d3iCmdIndex
d3iCmdIndex.description: A unique value for each DS3 card in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding DS3 card's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

d3iCmdMgtStationId.name: d3iCmdMgtStationId
d3iCmdMgtStationId.description: This object is a generic read-write variable that a Management Station (MS) can use to guarantee that the results from a command are the results of a command issued by that specific MS. Each MS must SET a unique value to this object when doing commands and GET the value of this object together with d3iCmdReqId and d3iCmdResult to detect interference from other MSs.

d3iCmdReqId.name: d3iCmdReqId
d3iCmdReqId.description: This object contains the value of the request-id field in the SNMP PDU which invoked the current or most recent command or test on this DS3 card. If the request-id is unknown or undefined, this object contains the value zero.

d3iCmdFunction.name: d3iCmdFunction
d3iCmdFunction.description: This object contains a value which describes the command which is being invoked.

d3iCmdForce.name: d3iCmdForce
d3iCmdForce.description: In some cases the DS3 card may be in a state such that certain commands could adversely affect connections. In such cases, a command request with this object not present or set to noForce will result in a warning. If the operator elects to ignore such warnings, this object can be set to force in a subsequent issue of the command to cause the command to be carried out regardless of its potentially hazzardous effects.

d3iCmdParam.name: d3iCmdParam
d3iCmdParam.description: This object contains parameters that are specific to the particular command being issued. In some cases, there will be no addtional parameters required.

d3iCmdResult.name: d3iCmdResult
d3iCmdResult.description: This object contains the result of the most recently requested command or test, or the value none(1) if no commands have been requested since the last reset.

d3iCmdCode.name: d3iCmdCode
d3iCmdCode.description: The value of this object upon commad completion indicates a futher description of what went wrong if the command was unsuccessful. In the case of tests, a bit mapped result of each of the sub-tests performed can be found in the status table.

d3iTeTable.name: d3iTeTable
d3iTeTable.description: The trap table containing an enable for each that the card is capable of generating. Some of these events occur often and traps may flood the network if care is not taken to avoid such conditions. These traps should be enabled sparingly.

d3iTeEntry.name: d3iTeEntry
d3iTeEntry.description: There is one entry for each DS3 card in the chassis.

d3iTeIndex.name: d3iTeIndex
d3iTeIndex.description: A unique value for each DS3 card in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding DS3 card's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

d3iTePbActive.name: d3iTePbActive
d3iTePbActive.description: Enables the Packet Bus Active Trap. Default is disableAll(2).

d3iTePbLost.name: d3iTePbLost
d3iTePbLost.description: Enables the Packet Bus lost Trap. Default is disableAll(2).

d3iTePbClockLossEvent.name: d3iTePbClockLossEvent
d3iTePbClockLossEvent.description: This object is used to disable the ability for a NAC to report when the packet bus clock has been lost. Defaule is diableAll(2).

d3iTePbClockRestoreEvent.name: d3iTePbClockRestoreEvent
d3iTePbClockRestoreEvent.description: This object is used to disable the ability for a NAC to report when the packet bus clock has been restored. Defaule is diableAll(2).

d3iTeTdmClockLost.name: d3iTeTdmClockLost
d3iTeTdmClockLost.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of TDM bus system clock lost. Default is disableAll(2).

d3iTeTdmClockRestored.name: d3iTeTdmClockRestored
d3iTeTdmClockRestored.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of TDM bus system clock restored. Default is disableAll(2).

d3iTeEnfasLinkUp.name: d3iTeEnfasLinkUp
d3iTeEnfasLinkUp.description: The trap enable for ENFAS link coming up trap. Default is disable.

d3iTeEnfasLinkDown.name: d3iTeEnfasLinkDown
d3iTeEnfasLinkDown.description: The trap enable for ENFAS link coming down trap. Default is disable.

d3iTeSystemReset.name: d3iTeSystemReset
d3iTeSystemReset.description: The trap enable disable for the DS3 system reset
